The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Navin death 

 Mumbai, July 8: Niranjan Hiranandani, managing director of Hiranandani Constructions, today denied reports of foul play or family dispute in his brother Navins death at his Malabar Hill flat yesterday.

 Navin was found dead by a domestic help in his apartment toilet. 

 Police suspect the doctor killed himself by slashing the upper part of his right arm with a surgical knife. They did not find a suicide note, but found the words heart attack no publicity scribbled on an envelope in his bedroom.

 Niranjan, 56, who runs the construction business with brother Surendra and son Darshan, said Navin was being treated for depression for 25 years and he believed it was a case of suicide. 




